Citation.sAbstract: Densities, n and speeds of sound, u of tetrahydropyran (i) + pyridine or a-, a- or a- picoline (j)  binary mixtures at (298.15, 303.15 and 308.15) K and excess molar enthalpies,HE of the same set of  mixtures at 308.15K have been measured as a function of composition using DSA 5000 densimeter and  2-drop micro calorimeter respectively. The resulting density and speed of sound data of the  investigated mixtures have been utilized to predict excess molar volumes,VE and excess isentropic  compressibilities,eSE. The observed data have been analyzed in terms of (i) Graph theory; and (ii)  Prigogine-Flory-Patterson theory. It has been observed that VE, HE and eSE data predicted by Graph  theory compare well with their experimental values.
Citation.sTitle: Thermodynamic properties of binary mixtures of tetrahydropyran with pyridine  and isomeric picolines: Excess molar volumes, excess molar enthalpies and excess  isentropic compressibilities
